  • Deprecated Classes 
    Class and Description
    org.bukkit.util.config.Configuration
    See YamlConfiguration
    org.bukkit.event.entity.EntityDamageByProjectileEvent
    use EntityDamageByEntityEvent instead, where EntityDamageByEntityEvent.getDamager() will return the Projectile
  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    org.bukkit.Server.createWorld(String, World.Environment)
    Use Server.createWorld(org.bukkit.WorldCreator)
    org.bukkit.Bukkit.createWorld(String, World.Environment)
    org.bukkit.Server.createWorld(String, World.Environment, ChunkGenerator)
    Use Server.createWorld(org.bukkit.WorldCreator)
    org.bukkit.Bukkit.createWorld(String, World.Environment, ChunkGenerator)
    org.bukkit.Server.createWorld(String, World.Environment, long)
    Use Server.createWorld(org.bukkit.WorldCreator)
    org.bukkit.Bukkit.createWorld(String, World.Environment, long)
    org.bukkit.Server.createWorld(String, World.Environment, long, ChunkGenerator)
    Use Server.createWorld(org.bukkit.WorldCreator)
    org.bukkit.Bukkit.createWorld(String, World.Environment, long, ChunkGenerator)
    org.bukkit.plugin.java.JavaPlugin.getConfiguration()
    See the new
    org.bukkit.block.Block.getFace(BlockFace)
    use Block.getRelative(BlockFace face)
    org.bukkit.block.Block.getFace(BlockFace, int)
    use Block.getRelative(BlockFace face, int distance)
    org.bukkit.World.getId()
    Replaced with World.getUID()
    org.bukkit.entity.Player.updateInventory()
    This method should not be relied upon as it is a temporary work-around for a larger, more complicated issue.
